## The Englander Showdown (Spring 2007)

### Background: The 2003 Defection

- 2003: **Belopolsky** and **Volfbeyn** quit to join **Israel Englander's** Millennium Management
- Simons had stormed into Englander's NYC office demanding their termination

> "Show me the proof." — Englander to Simons (asking for evidence of theft)

- Englander privately wondered if Simons' real fear was additional departures
- Simons wouldn't share much with rival
- Renaissance sued Englander's firm + Volfbeyn/Belopolsky; they countersued

### The 2007 Confrontation

- Late spring 2007: Simons in Englander's office (41-story glass building near Grand Central)
- **Israel Englander**: graying, 57, billionaire in tortoiseshell glasses
- Tense, miserable, angry at each other

### Volfbeyn and Belopolsky's Success

- Four years post-defection: researchers set up quantitative system at Millennium
- Racked up **~$100M profits**, became some of Englander's most successful traders
- Signed nondisclosure agreements prohibiting use/sharing of Medallion secrets
- Refused to sign noncompete (viewed as underhanded—slipped into paper pile)
- With no signed noncompete, Englander figured he could hire them if they didn't use Renaissance secrets

### Evidence Mounts

- Englander claimed researchers relied on open-source software and academic papers (not Renaissance IP)
- Simons furious and worried—their trading could eat into Medallion profits
- Principle at stake: *They stole from me!*
- Evidence emerged: Volfbeyn/Belopolsky may have taken Medallion's IP
- Independent expert: used much of same source code as Medallion
- Similar mathematical model to measure market impact of trades
- One expert witness refused to testify on their behalf (too skeptical)
- One strategy called **"Henry's signal"** (developed by **Henry Laufer**)

### Settlement (Months Later)

- Simons and Englander made little headway that day
- Months later: deal reached
- Englander's firm terminated Volfbeyn/Belopolsky, paid Renaissance **$20M**
- Some within Renaissance incensed—renegades had made **$20M+ trading for Englander**
- After break of several years, they'd resume activities
- Simons relieved to end dispute, send warning to would-be followers

